webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) The new church in Hägerstad was erected in 1864-66 after drawings by Carl Gustaf Blom-Carlsson. The architect created a completely through neo-Gothic creation. His original proposal was not entirely implemented, yet the church is an example of the architectural conception of the time. The buildings to the west of the church served at the time as a bell settlement and the parish church school - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000028. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021018235673. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
